@startuml network-detection-flow
!include _standard-style.puml

title Network Location Detection (Unified)

participant "Coordinator\n(health-coordinator.js)" as coord
participant "dig CLI\n(fresh DNS)" as dig
participant "VPN CLI\n(/opt/cisco)" as vpn
participant "TCP probe\n(PAC host)" as tcp

== Every 15s tick ==

coord -> dig: dig +short muc.proxy-pac.bmwgroup.net\n(fresh process = current OS DNS)
alt DNS resolves (e.g. 160.50.180.101)
  dig --> coord: IP address
  coord -> vpn: /opt/cisco/secureclient/bin/vpn status
  alt output contains "Connected"
    vpn --> coord: Connected
    coord -> coord: location = **vpn**
  else Disconnected (office LAN, no VPN)
    vpn --> coord: Disconnected
    coord -> tcp: TCP connect to PAC IP, port 80
    tcp --> coord: latency (e.g. 13ms)
    alt latency < 100ms
      coord -> coord: location = **corporate**\n(on-site LAN)
    else latency ≥ 100ms
      coord -> coord: location = **vpn**\n(tunnelled, high latency)
    end
  end
else DNS fails (NXDOMAIN / timeout)
  dig --> coord: (empty)
  coord -> coord: location = **open**\n(home / public network)
end

note over coord
  **Key fix**: Uses `dig` (spawns fresh process)
  instead of Node.js `dns.Resolver` which
  caches DNS servers from process startup.

  On office LAN without VPN:
  • VPN CLI = "Disconnected"
  • PAC DNS resolves (corporate DNS)
  • TCP latency < 100ms
  → Correctly detects **corporate**
end note

@enduml
